<TITLE> Saifur Rahman's <i>janaza</i> to be followed by 3 days of mourning </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 5 (bdnews24.com)The namaj-e-janaza of former finance minister M Saifur Rahman will be held in front of the BNP central office in Naya Paltan at 12:30pm on Sunday before moving to the south plaza of the parliament complex at 2:30pm, a party official has said. BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia discussed the funeral arrangements with the late politician's relatives at their Gulshan residence, BNP office secretary Rizvi Ahmed and chief whip Joynal Abdin Farrouque told reporters Saturday night outside the family home in Dhaka. Family members said the timing of the burial would be finalised when the late politician's eldest son, Naser Rahman, arrived from Saudi Arabia on Sunday, after which the body would be buried at the family plot in Baharmordan, Moulavibazar. The main opposition BNP has also declared a three-day period of mourning, from Sunday. Party flags are to be flown at half-mast throughout the country, and black flags hoisted at party offices over the three day period, party officials said. Milad mahfil will be held in memory of the veteran party leader at BNP offices across the country, Rizvi Ahmed told bdnews24.com. Saifur Rahman was declared dead at Brahmanbaria General Hospital on Saturday afternoon after his car crashed on the Dhaka-Sylhet highway. A police escort accompanied Rahman's remains to his Gulshan residence, where they arrived at 7:45pm. bdnews24.com
